last_episode_to_air.overview: Seven years from now, a lot has changed for Bob, Abishola and their friends and family as they reflect on how far they've come and consider what's most important to them as they head into the future.
last_episode_to_air.name: Find Your Bench

name: Bob Hearts Abishola
overview: A love story about a middle-aged compression sock businessman from Detroit who unexpectedly falls for his cardiac nurse, a Nigerian immigrant, while recovering from a heart attack and sets his sights on winning her over.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Undaunted by Abishola’s lack of initial interest or the vast differences in their backgrounds, Bob is determined to win Abishola’s heart.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Season three picks up with Bob and Abishola’s arrival in Lagos – surprising, like everything else in this unconventional, cross-cultural love story!

tagline: A love story made in America.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: An American man falls in love with his Nigerian nurse.

episodes.name: Nigerians Don't Do Useless Things
episodes.overview: While Bob waits for Abishola to make the next move, her Auntie Olu and Uncle Tunde make it hard for her by stalking him.

episodes.name: A Bird May Love A Fish
episodes.overview: Bob attempts to learn more about Nigerian customs while Abishola has to contend with gossip spreading about her relationship with Bob.

episodes.name: Square Hamburger, Round Buns
episodes.overview: After Abishola calls off things with Bob, her Auntie Olu sets her up with a Nigerian pharmacist, and Bob tries online dating.

episodes.name: Whacking the Mole
episodes.overview: After Abishola has a romantic dream about Bob, she tries to suppress her feelings for him and pays the price.

episodes.name: Ralph Lauren and Fish
episodes.overview: Bob and Abishola finally go on a proper date, which is interrupted by Dottie's medical emergency.

episodes.name: Tough Like a Laundromat Washing Machine
episodes.overview: Bob hires Abishola to take care of Dottie in his home while she recovers. Dottie has a hard time dealing with her limitations and takes it out on Abishola.

episodes.name: Useless Potheads
episodes.overview: With Abishola only helping part-time, Bob, Douglas and Christina struggle to take care of Dottie.

episodes.name: We Were Beggars, Now We Are Choosers
episodes.overview: After Abishola gives her previous suitor a second chance, Uncle Tunde goes behind Auntie Olu's back to warn Bob about the other man who's courting his niece.

episodes.name: Ice Cream for Breakfast
episodes.overview: Bob must gain the confidence to fight for Abishola when she goes on another date with Chukwuemeka. Also, Uncle Tunde finds an unlikely friend in Dottie in the aftermath of his fight with Auntie Olu.

episodes.name: Splitting the Hairs
episodes.overview: Bob, Douglas and Christina try to get Dottie to make a will; Abishola and Kemi's friendship is tested after Abishola catches Kemi in a lie.

episodes.name: There's My Nigerians
episodes.overview: While Bob and Abishola struggle to pull Dottie out of her depression, Auntie Olu and Uncle Tunde come over to lift her spirits.

episodes.name: The Canadians of Africa
episodes.overview: Abishola doesn't appreciate it when Bob gives her unsolicited parenting advice about her "unhappy son".

episodes.name: Full-Frontal Dottie
episodes.overview: Excited by her physical therapy progress, Dottie insists she is ready to return to MaxDot, much to the dismay of Bob, Douglas and Christina.

episodes.name: Black Ice
episodes.overview: On Valentine's Day, when it comes to showing affection, Bob and Abishola have to find a way to meet each other in the middle.

episodes.name: Where's Your Other Wives, Tunde?
episodes.overview: Dottie, Auntie Olu and Uncle Tunde must find a way to reconcile when they're forced to eat dinner together. Also, Bob and Abishola have differing opinions on the progress of their relationship.

episodes.name: A Big, White Thumb
episodes.overview: Abishola takes her relationship with Bob to the next level when she invites him into an intimate part of her life: church. Also, Kemi fights with Ogechi to be Chukwuemeka's favorite.

episodes.name: Sock Wife
episodes.overview: Bob's past and present collide when his ex-wife, Lorraine, is admitted to Abishola's hospital. Also, Christina recruits Kofo for a project to rename the sock colors.

episodes.name: Angry, Happy, Same Face
episodes.overview: Abishola must draw the line when Bob's ex-wife, Lorraine, tries to maneuver her way back into Bob's life. Also, Goodwin is concerned when Christina sets her romantic sights on Kofo.

episodes.name: Randy's a Wrangler
episodes.overview: Dottie makes an unexpected connection when she meets a fellow stroke survivor, Hank (John Ratzenberger), at physical therapy. Also, Bob and Douglas try to keep tabs on Christina while she's away at an emotional wellness spa.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Undaunted by Abishola’s lack of initial interest or the vast differences in their backgrounds, Bob is determined to win Abishola’s heart.

episodes.name: On a Dead Guy's Bench
episodes.overview: Bob enlists Tunde’s help to buy an engagement ring, but his plans to propose to Abishola are upended by her belief that a traditional marriage is more trouble than it’s worth.

episodes.name: Paris is for Lovers, Not Mothers
episodes.overview: Kemi leans on Abishola after an argument with Chukwuemeka, disrupting her and Bob’s engagement celebration. Also, Dottie gives Douglas a new job at MaxDot,

episodes.name: Straight Outta Lagos
episodes.overview: Bob is excited to show off Abishola at his industry awards gala, but ruins the evening when he doesn't let her speak for herself. Also, Douglas tries fitting in with Goodwin and Kofo as one of the blue-collar guys on the warehouse floor.

episodes.name: Camp Bananas
episodes.overview: For the sake of Bob's health, Bob and Abishola try reducing stress by taking a day off together. Also, Christina is boss for the day at MaxDot, and Gloria steps in to care for Dottie.

episodes.name: Sleeping Next to an Old Boat
episodes.overview: Abishola worries that Bob's privileged lifestyle is starting to rub off on Dele. Also, a new robot vacuum brings Tunde joy but begins to make Olu feel insecure.

episodes.name: A Tight A* is a Wonderful Thing
episodes.overview: Thanks to Abishola's brutal Nigerian honesty, Bob finds himself in a feud with Kemi. Also, after Douglas makes a big mistake on the warehouse floor, Goodwin hates himself for looking the other way.

episodes.name: The Wrong Adebambo
episodes.overview: Abishola's husband makes a surprise visit and Bob sees this as a perfect opportunity for Abishola to ask for a divorce, but Abishola is surprised when old feelings for her husband return.

episodes.name: Honest Yak Prices
episodes.overview: Abishola's husband says he'll never agree to a divorce so as a result, Bob and Abishola are upset that they will never get married.

episodes.name: Tunde the Boy King
episodes.overview: After a chance encounter, Abishola and Christina unexpectedly hit it off as future sisters-in-law. Also, at MaxDot, Douglas gives the workers a much needed morale boost, but feels pressured when Bob praises him as a natural leader.

episodes.name: The Cheerleader Leader
episodes.overview: After Tayo forbids Dele from dancing, Abishola enlists Bob's help in talking to Dele about his feelings.

episodes.name: I Did Not Raise Him to Be a Teenager
episodes.overview: When Abishola puts her foot down about Dele not going to Nigeria with his father, Dele rebels against her for the very first time.

episodes.name: We Don't Rat on Family
episodes.overview: Bob prepares to meet Abishola's mother but gets more than he bargained for when he enlists Tunde's help in securing her approval. Also, Abishola considers breaking Nigerian tradition by having a small wedding.

episodes.name: A Big African Bassoon
episodes.overview: When Gloria goes on vacation, Abishola takes charge of the nursing staff, but quickly falls short as the job requires "people skills." Also, with Abishola extra busy at the hospital, the Wheelers try to cope with her temporary absence.

episodes.name: A Tough Old Bird
episodes.overview: Bob and Abishola try to help a sad and volatile Kemi who, after being dumped by Chukwuemeka, struggles with the possibility that her happiest days might be behind her.

episodes.name: TLC: Tunde's Loving Care
episodes.overview: Abishola begins studying for medical school, she offends Gloria with an insensitive comment about Gloria's own journey of almost becoming a doctor. Also, Tunde schools a reluctant Bob on the art of home repair while helping to fix his dishwasher.

episodes.name: Sights and Bites
episodes.overview: Abishola is nervous about Dele's trip to Nigeria with his father. Also, Bob creates a guidebook on Nigeria for Dele that he proudly calls "Sights and Bites."

episodes.name: The Devil's Taste Buds
episodes.overview: While Dele is in Nigeria with his dad, Abishola struggles with how to handle her free time, so Bob, Gloria and Kemi remind her how to let loose. Also, Dottie enlists Christina's help at her old house and Olu and Tunde try to keep up with their new Nigerian houseguest..

episodes.name: God Accepts Venmo
episodes.overview: While comparing their busy schedules, Bob and Abishola realize the perfect date for their wedding is in just three weeks and enlist their family and friends to help plan their big day.

episodes.name: Welcome to Lagos
episodes.overview: After Bob and Abishola land in Lagos, they rush to rescue Dele from his dad's place. Auntie Olu and Uncle Tunde explore their old stomping grounds and realize things have changed since their last visit to Nigeria.

episodes.name: Bowango
episodes.overview: With a traditional Nigerian wedding approaching, the Wheelers are formally introduced to Abishola's family; Bob tries to demonstrate his serious intentions of marrying Abishola; Abishola tries to keep the peace between her mother and Auntie Olu.

episodes.name: Dud
episodes.overview: After returning home from their wedding in Nigeria, Abishola moves into Bob's house, and with his blessing, she redecorates to make the place her own.

episodes.name: Old Strokey
episodes.overview: With Bob and Abishola settling into married life, Dottie feels pushed aside and decides to run away from home. Also, Goodwin and Kofo bring a domestic dispute to MaxDot.

episodes.name: Greasy Badge of Honor
episodes.overview: After indulging in a luxurious girls' day with Dottie and Christina, Abishola worries she's losing touch with her humble Nigerian roots. Also, Goodwin feels threatened when Kofo gets a pitch meeting with Bob.

episodes.name: The Devil's Throuple
episodes.overview: Abishola is caught in the middle when Morenike agrees to be the "plus one" in Kemi and Chukwuemeka's relationship. Also, when Bob refuses to pay for Douglas' company car, he learns what it's like to live on a budget.

episodes.name: Fumble in the Dark
episodes.overview: Abishola and Kemi are conflicted as to how to handle Morenike after she confides her deepest secret to them. Also, when Bob gets credit for Christina's idea for a Twitter marketing campaign, she considers leaving MaxDot.

episodes.name: Light Duty
episodes.overview: Abishola and Kemi take a directionless Christina to see a Yoruba priest, where she learns that her toxic relationship with her mother may be stifling her growth. Also, Bob deals with the fallout of promoting Kofo over Goodwin when Goodwin has a panic attack at work.

episodes.name: I'm Not Edsel
episodes.overview: Abishola gets the surprise of a lifetime when she finds out Bob has flown in Dele and her mother, Ebun, from Nigeria. However, the joy is cut short when Ebun's constant criticism makes Bob question his success as a businessman.

episodes.name: Tunde123
episodes.overview: When Abishola finds out Tayo has given Dele a credit card, she worries he's being spoiled and becomes stricter with him. Also, worried she's being too harsh, Bob goes behind Abishola's back to do something special for Dele.

episodes.name: Cats in a Bathtub
episodes.overview: When Bob accidentally reveals Morenike is gay, Abishola and Kemi are forced to defend her against their church, and even their own families. Also, Douglas comes clean to Olivia about not being poor.

episodes.name: Your Beans are Flatlining
episodes.overview: Bob is surprised when Abishola's medical school plans include going to Baltimore - with or without him.

episodes.name: One Man, No Baby
episodes.overview: When word gets out that Bob and Abishola might be trying to have a baby, the expectations from family, friends and employees start to take a toll on the couple.

episodes.name: Every Subpoena is a Tiny Hug
episodes.overview: When Christina gets a new job at a sock startup, the family is supportive until they find out the new company is more successful than MaxDot. Realizing they've given their competitor a helping hand, Dottie vows to do anything to get her daughter back.

episodes.name: Compress to Impress
episodes.overview: Bob's not sure his family is cut out for the small screen when he decides to shoot a TV commercial for MaxDot and the director, Marion, wants the ad to focus on the Wheelers.

episodes.name: I'll Sleep When I'm Dead
episodes.overview: Dottie and Goodwin question Bob's ability to lead under pressure when the successful MaxDot television commercial generates more business than they can handle. Also, Abishola is unsure if Bob's newfound success is worth it if it means he's never home.

episodes.name: Inappropriate Nakedness
episodes.overview: Bob and Abishola decide her mother has officially overstayed her welcome when Ebunoluwa starts renovating Bob's guest room.Also, when Abishola and Kemi hatch a plan to have a spirit speak to Ebunoluwa from beyond the grave, Abishola gets more information about her mother than she bargained for.

episodes.name: Greasy Underdog
episodes.overview: When Bob, Abishola and Kemi learn that Morenike's family disowned her because she's gay, they do what they can to help her pay for school and stay in America.

episodes.name: Who Raised You
episodes.overview: Douglas is finally ready to introduce Olivia to his family, but he sets some ground rules to make sure Dottie plays nice.

episodes.name: Wrangling a Greased Pig
episodes.overview: When Abishola brings Dele to work with her at the hospital, she discovers that her dream of him becoming a doctor might not become a reality; Kemi and Chukwuemeka's mothers bond when Ogechi slips in the bathtub.

episodes.name: A Little Slap and Tickle
episodes.overview: With Dele's dream of becoming a doctor dashed, Bob, Abishola, Tayo and the rest of the family scramble to find him a new career path -- but when the pressure mounts, Dele turns to a surprising source for advice on dealing with his family.

episodes.name: Beard In Her Pulpit
episodes.overview: When a charismatic new pastor joins the congregation, Abishola takes a new interest in church; after Dottie gives out bonuses to upper management, but not Goodwin, Bob must do what he can to make sure he doesn't lose his best employee.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: Season three picks up with Bob and Abishola’s arrival in Lagos – surprising, like everything else in this unconventional, cross-cultural love story!

episodes.name: Touched by a Holy Hand
episodes.overview: Abishola and Kemi hatch a plan to keep Ebun and the new pastor’s flirtation from growing; Bob is thrown for a loop when Goodwin leaves MaxDot for a better job at Christina’s company.

episodes.name: Bibles to Brothels
episodes.overview: Bob reconsiders his future at MaxDot and seeks advice from an unexpected source, while Abishola questions Bob’s erratic behavior.

episodes.name: Americans and Their Dreams
episodes.overview: After Bob takes a step back from his busy work life, he decides to buy a boat to enjoy during his free time. Also, a newspaper reporter comes to MaxDot to interview Goodwin.

episodes.name: Inner Boss Bitch
episodes.overview: Having spurned her family when she quit MaxDot, Christina turns to Abishola when she's fired from Toesey Woesies; Bob and Uncle Tunde go fishing.

episodes.name: Kicked Outta the Dele Club
episodes.overview: Bob lets Dele get a new haircut and finds himself caught between an irate Abishola and a surprisingly stubborn Dele; Dottie runs into difficulties with the MaxDot board of directors.

episodes.name: Two Rusty Tractors
episodes.overview: Abishola is thrilled when Bob gets back to work and goes on an impromptu road trip with Goodwin.

episodes.name: Your Father's Kingdom
episodes.overview: Abishola turns to Gloria and Kemi when Bob mortgages their home to pay for a new factory space. Also, Kemi worries that she and Chukwuemeka are losing their spark.

episodes.name: Estée Lauder and Goat Meat
episodes.overview: Bob enlists Tunde’s help to renovate the factory. Also, Abishola tries to cheer up Ebunoluwa with a party after she receives bad news from Nigeria.

episodes.name: Idle Nigerians
episodes.overview: Abishola's visit to the sock factory during a nurse's strike puts extra pressure on Bob to make the factory successful.

episodes.name: An Afro and a Peugeot
episodes.overview: Bob and Abishola are at odds over whether Dele is ready to get behind the wheel and decide to take matters into their own hands. Also, Christina offers Douglas some work advice only to watch him claim her ideas as his own.

episodes.name: Twerk O' Clock
episodes.overview: When Bob alerts MaxDot’s longtime friend and sock manufacturer that he will no longer need their services, Dottie steps in to try to salvage their relationship. Also, Abishola tries to manage her discomfort while attending a drag brunch with Olu and Morenike.

episodes.name: My Successful Lawyer Son
episodes.overview: Abishola gets a taste of Kemi’s new personality when her successful lawyer son comes to visit.

episodes.name: Happy People Are Lazy
episodes.overview: Abishola decides to postpone taking the Medical College Admission Test. Christina grapples with taking a job opportunity.

episodes.name: Put That Toe on Ice
episodes.overview: Bob and Abishola attempt to find time together amidst their busy schedules. Also, Goodwin’s leadership tactics push Kofo over the edge.

episodes.name: Every Character is the Villain
episodes.overview: Bob makes things worse after interfering in Goodwin and Kofo’s ongoing spat. Also, Abishola puts her pride on the line when she realizes she’s been an inattentive friend to Kemi.

episodes.name: Mmm, Fresh Baked Sock!
episodes.overview: Abishola must reconcile a decade-old wound when she’s forced to attend the funeral of an unlikable aunt. Also, Bob struggles at the factory with the first batch of socks before receiving support from an unlikely source.

episodes.name: A Hundred CCs of Handsome
episodes.overview: When Abishola learns that Bob talked Chukwuemeka into proposing to Kemi, she tries to fix the situation. Kofo permanently alters his relationship with Goodwin when he considers signing a lease in Olu and Tunde’s apartment building.

episodes.name: Keep that Under Your Gele
episodes.overview: When Bob asks for space from his ever-present mother, Dottie doesn’t take it well. Also, Kofo attempts to enjoy the luxuries of living alone but his new landlord, Tunde, overstays his welcome.

episodes.name: The Genius Who Fell Out of My Womb
episodes.overview: Bob is thrilled to share a day at his alma mater with Abishola and Dele, but his university doesn’t meet Abishola’s Ivy League standards.

episodes.name: Take Two Yellows and Go to Bed
episodes.overview: Bob’s grand opening party for the sock factory is upstaged by a fight between Abishola and her sister-in-law.

episodes.name: Uncharted Waters of Mediocrity
episodes.overview: Doubts begin to creep in as Abishola awaits her acceptance to medical school in Baltimore. Bob battles his subconscious.

episodes.name: The Dead Eyes of a Respectful Son
episodes.overview: When Abishola finds out Dele cancelled his plans to go to Harvard behind her back, Bob steps in to keep her from going ballistic.

episodes.name: Kill the Cat
episodes.overview: After Tunde gets into a car accident, Bob and Abishola cajole him into getting glasses but worry that his issues are more than just his eyesight.

episodes.name: The Devil's Hot Tub
episodes.overview: Abishola and Kemi's friendship is pushed to the edge when Kemi wants to disregard Nigerian tradition and have a Las Vegas wedding. Also, Bob and the Wheelers have to avert a strike at MaxDot before it sinks the family business.

episodes.name: The Heart Attack Boys
episodes.overview: When Christina tells her family that she's decided to have a baby by herself, Bob and Abishola start to reconsider whether to have a baby of their own as well.

episodes.name: Tayo Time
episodes.overview: When Abishola's ex-husband, Tayo, visits Detroit for work, everyone falls under his spell except Bob and Abishola, who know there must be more to his visit than he claims.

episodes.name: A Tablespoon of Dad
episodes.overview: When Dottie moves her husband Max's urn into Bob and Abishola's living room, everyone is forced to confront their views on death and the afterlife. Also, Goodwin pits Douglas and Kofo against each other in a battle for Dottie's vacant MaxDot office.

episodes.name: Worth the Cooties
episodes.overview: After Christina kicks Abishola and Dottie out for making light of her pre-pregnancy preparations, Christina bonds with Douglas and Abishola spends a fun day with Dottie. Also, when Bob, Goodwin and Kofo are stumped on a work issue, Bob insists they go out to lunch to loosen up.

episodes.name: My Michelle Obama
episodes.overview: When Ebun attempts to establish herself as matriarch, Olu worries she's losing her place in the family; Bob and Abishola are forced to choose sides. Also, Tunde is appointed interim deacon at church.

episodes.name: Sad Cupcakes
episodes.overview: When Bob receives an offer to sell MaxDot, he must weigh the potential payout against his family's legacy. Also, when the hospital cuts nursing staff, Abishola and Gloria's relationship is strained.

episodes.name: Diamonds Are Made to Sparkle
episodes.overview: When Bob second-guesses selling MaxDot, a new buyer presents a compelling offer. Also, the prospect of new wealth has Abishola stuck between her conservative nature to hide it and Nigerian pressure to flaunt it.

episodes.name: These Giants Are Flexible
episodes.overview: When Bob and Abishola go to New York City with Dele for his Juilliard audition, Abishola reconnects with her brother Ade.

episodes.name: Olu! I Popped!
episodes.overview: Bob and Abishola plan a trip to Las Vegas for Kemi's wedding and Kemi and Chukwuemeka get into an argument over his mother.

episodes.name: Find Your Bench
episodes.overview: Seven years from now, a lot has changed for Bob, Abishola and their friends and family as they reflect on how far they've come and consider what's most important to them as they head into the future.
